This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with video classification using deep learning models. The paper also discusses the reduction of model size and computational intensity, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of linear algebra techniques in deep learning models may also make it relevant to the Mathematical Methods in Computer Science (cs.MM) sub-category. The paper's focus on video classification may also make it relevant to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the use of state-of-the-art network architectures and thorough experiments may make it relevant to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
